    "en": {
      "title": "7 of the police are sworn in as lawyers",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "According to the police headquarters, seven officers working in the police department were sworn in as lawyers in the Supreme Court recently.",
        "Among these people are an Assistant Superintendent of Police, a Chief Inspector of Police, three police inspectors, a sub-inspector and a sub-inspector, the police said.",
        "Assistant Superintendent of Police MPC Chanaka De Silva (Criminal Investigation Department) Chief Inspector Sitara Sanjay Perera (Kalutara Police Training College), Police Inspector PKRM, Vasantha Kumara (Legal Division), Police Inspector S. W APR Samarawickrama (Legal Division), Police Inspector W GB Kumarasinghe (Central Province Legal Division), Police Inspector PMC Sandaruwan (Legal Division), Sub Inspector MDC Jayamini (North Western Province Legal Division) Gentlemen have thus taken oath as lawyers."
      ],
